Now, after 7 weeks, the #Jets rank counting only ZW starts.

Zach Wilson takes this offense from bad with Flacco to middle of the pack (or better if he improves).

#nflverse https://t.co/ypMhdR4uQN

Snap Counts Pillboxes!! Here's the Chiefs offense in their mollywhopping of the Niners. Pacheco, the nominal starter, got the fewest snaps of the RB's, even with the three meaningless snaps to end the game. Hardman led WR's in snaps. Moores snaps dropped. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/RMxyEbji7k

Here's the Chiefs defense. Lammons in on three money downs (before garbage time). Gay sat out two entire drives, replaced by Harris first, then by Cook. Wow, after the Moore flub, Jones, Clark, and Karlaftis all sat that entire drive (ended in TD). ðŸ¤· 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/7VHQyebuya

Here's the Niners charts. CMC not in for any 3rd downs. In fact, it looks like Juszczyk is their 3rd down back? Greenlaw left after the first drive of the 3rd qtr, replced by Flannigan-Fowles. 

#nflverse #rstats https://t.co/Las2M8MifI

NFL division records excluding divisional games through seven weeks. Eagles at 6-0 somehow can't get any breathing room in the NFC East, who have won 84% of their non-divisional matchups so far. NFC East and AFC East beating up on the rest of the league #nflverse https://t.co/yzju6elgWX

Plus, the new absolute gel edition, that highlights close games via absolute score difference and also gel electrophoresis!

#nflverse https://t.co/yyFtkO2wNJ

Just for fun, here's a chart showing the average field position for each team on kickoffs they fielded in the end zone, and thus could have knelt for touchback, but didn't. I present this data without comment.
